Installing Eggdrop
==================

Build system: Meson + Ninja. The traditional autoconf/make workflow
is not present in this fork.


Dependencies
------------

Required:
  - Meson >= 0.57
  - Ninja
  - C compiler with C23 support (GCC 11+, Clang 13+)

Optional (auto-detected):
  - Tcl >= 8.6 dev headers     Tcl scripting
  - Python >= 3.8 dev headers  Python scripting module
  - zlib dev headers            compress module
  - liburing                    io_uring backend (Linux only)

Bundled (no install needed):
  - opssl                       TLS 1.2/1.3
  - LMDB                        Crash-safe storage (in libop)

At least one of Tcl or Python should be present for scripting.


Platform packages
-----------------

Debian / Ubuntu:

    sudo apt-get install meson ninja-build
    sudo apt-get install tcl-dev libssl-dev python3-dev zlib1g-dev  # optional

Fedora / RHEL:

    sudo dnf install meson ninja-build
    sudo dnf install tcl-devel openssl-devel python3-devel zlib-devel  # optional

macOS (Homebrew):

    brew install meson ninja
    brew install tcl-tk openssl@3 python@3.12 zlib  # optional
    export PKG_CONFIG_PATH="$(brew --prefix openssl@3)/lib/pkgconfig:\
    $(brew --prefix tcl-tk)/lib/pkgconfig:$PKG_CONFIG_PATH"

MSYS2 / MinGW-w64 (UCRT64 shell):

    pacman -S mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-meson mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-ninja
    pacman -S mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-tcl mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-openssl \
              mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-python mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-zlib  # optional

MSVC (Visual Studio 2019+):

    1. Install "Desktop development with C++" workload
    2. pip install meson ninja
    3. Install vcpkg:
         git clone https://github.com/microsoft/vcpkg C:\vcpkg
         C:\vcpkg\bootstrap-vcpkg.bat
    4. Install optional deps:
         C:\vcpkg\vcpkg install tcl:x64-windows openssl:x64-windows \
           zlib:x64-windows python3:x64-windows
    5. Open "x64 Native Tools Command Prompt" and set:
         set VCPKG=C:\vcpkg\installed\x64-windows
         set PKG_CONFIG_PATH=%VCPKG%\lib\pkgconfig
         set PATH=%VCPKG%\bin;%VCPKG%\tools\pkgconf;%PATH%

Cygwin:

    Install via setup: meson, gcc-core, ninja, tcl-devel, libssl-devel,
    python3-devel, zlib-devel, git


Build
-----

    # Configure
    meson setup build/

    # Compile
    ninja -C build/ -j$(nproc)

    # Install (default prefix: /usr/local)
    ninja -C build/ install

Common configure options:

    meson setup build/ -Dtcl=disabled         # no Tcl
    meson setup build/ -Dipv6=true            # IPv6
    meson setup build/ -Dtls=enabled          # TLS (default)
    meson setup build/ -Dpython=auto          # Python
    meson setup build/ -Degg-debug=true       # ASAN + UBSAN
    meson setup build/ --prefix=$HOME/eggdrop # custom prefix

See all options: meson configure build/


Setup
-----

Option A — interactive wizard (recommended):

    ./eggdrop --setup mybot.toml

Option B — copy and edit sample:

    cp eggdrop-basic.toml mybot.toml
    $EDITOR mybot.toml

Option C — migrate existing .conf:

    python3 scripts/conf2toml.py mybot.conf mybot.toml


First run
---------

    ./eggdrop -m mybot.toml     # creates userfile
    ./eggdrop mybot.toml        # subsequent runs

No chmod or shebang needed for TOML configs.


TLS certificates
----------------

See doc/TLS for certificate generation after installing.


Auto-restart
------------

    ./scripts/autobotchk mybot.toml -systemd   # systemd
    ./scripts/autobotchk mybot.toml             # crontab


I/O backends
------------

Auto-selected at configure time:

    Platform             Backend
    -------------------- ----------
    Linux >= 5.1         io_uring
    Linux                epoll
    macOS / BSD          kqueue
    Windows native       IOCP
    Cygwin / fallback    select()


Debug builds
------------

    meson setup build-debug/ -Degg-debug=true
    ninja -C build-debug/


Modules
-------

All modules build by default. Disable individually:

    meson setup build/ -Dmodule-compress=false -Dmodule-python=false

List module options: meson configure build/ | grep module-


